# CODEX: ORKS — FACTION RULES

---

## ORK SPECIAL RULES

### Mob Rule

Orks don't run because they're scared — they run because nobody's watchin'. Or sometimes they don't run at all. Sometimes they do something much, much worse.

**MOB SIZE AS LEADERSHIP:** An Ork unit may use the number of models currently in the unit as its **LEADERSHIP** value for **MORALE** and **PINNING** tests, up to a maximum of 10. The unit may always choose to use its base Leadership from its **DATASHEET** profile instead, if it is higher.

**DA MOB AIN'T DONE YET:** If an Ork unit fails a **MORALE** or **PINNING** test even after applying Mob Rule, the unit does not fall back or become pinned as normal. Instead, roll on the **MOB RULE TABLE** below to determine what happens. The result replaces the normal consequences of the failed test.

**Da Mob Rule Table (D20)**

| D20 | Name | Result |
| :---: | :---- | :---- |
| 1 | **Every Ork for 'Imself!** | The mob scatters. The unit immediately falls back 2D6" as normal. Additionally, the unit may not use Mob Rule for the remainder of the game — they've properly lost their nerve. |
| 2 | **Trampled in da Rush** | The boyz panic and stampede over each other. The unit suffers D3 Strength 4 AP— hits, randomly allocated, with no cover saves allowed. The unit then counts as **PINNED**. |
| 3 | **'Oo's da Boss?** | Two Orks start arguing over who's in charge. The unit may not shoot or charge this turn and next turn while the argument is resolved. At the end of the following turn, the unit regains normal function. If the unit contains a **CHARACTER**, ignore this result and treat as **Got Sumfin' ta Prove** instead. |
| 4 | **Shiny Fings!** | The boyz get distracted by the nearest piece of terrain or wreckage. The unit immediately moves D6" toward the nearest terrain feature (not occupied by enemy models), stopping if this would bring them into base contact with enemy models. The unit counts as having moved and may not shoot this phase. |
| 5 | **Blame da Grot** | The Orks turn on the weakest member of the mob. Remove one model of the controlling player's choice from the unit (this does not cause further morale tests). The unit then passes the morale test and may act normally. |
| 6 | **Grotz to da Front!** | Survival instinct kicks in. The unit immediately goes to ground (**TAKE COVER!**) whether they want to or not. They gain +2 to cover saves instead of the usual +1. |
| 7 | **Leg It… Dat Way!** | The boyz run, but in the wrong direction. The unit moves 2D6" directly toward the nearest enemy unit. If this brings them into base contact with enemy models, they count as having charged (but gain no charge bonuses). |
| 8 | **Da Boss Sez Stay!** | Nothing happens. The boyz mill about in confusion but hold their ground. The unit may not advance, shoot, or charge this turn but does not fall back. |
| 9 | **Mork's Disapproval** | A strange feeling washes over the mob. All Ork units (friend and foe) within 6" must immediately take a **PINNING** test. The original unit counts as passing its morale test after this effect resolves. |
| 10 | **Squig Loose!** | Something gets loose from someone's pack. Place a marker in base contact with the unit. The marker moves 2D6" in a random direction at the start of each subsequent Ork turn. Any unit (friend or enemy) it contacts suffers D3 Strength 3 AP— hits. The squig is removed if any model directs an attack at it (no roll needed) or at the end of the game. The original unit passes its morale test. |
| 11 | **'Ere We Go!** | The boyz channel their fear into forward momentum. The unit immediately passes its morale test and gains ***Fleet*** until the end of the turn. If the unit is eligible to charge, it must attempt to charge the nearest enemy unit. |
| 12 | **Ded 'Ard** | Orkish stubbornness kicks in. The unit passes its morale test and gains ***Fearless*** until the end of the next player turn. |
| 13 | **Get Stuck In!** | The unit passes its morale test and immediately gains +1 Attack until the end of the turn. This bonus is cumulative with charge bonuses. |
| 14 | **Loot Da Bodies!** | The boyz start picking through the carnage. The unit passes its morale test. If there are any destroyed vehicle wrecks or dead Monstrous Creature models within 6", the unit may immediately move up to 6" toward the nearest one. Models in the unit gain +1 to their armor save (to a maximum of 3+) for the remainder of the game, representing looted scrap armor. |
| 15 | **Got Sumfin' ta Prove** | The boyz rally hard. The unit passes its morale test and gains +1 WS and +1 BS until the end of the turn as they fight to impress the Boss. |
| 16 | **WAAAGH! Spark** | The near-rout ignites something primal. The unit passes its morale test. The controlling player gains +2 **WAAAGH! ENERGY**. |
| 17 | **Seein' Red** | The boyz go berserk. The unit passes its morale test and gains ***Rage*** and ***Furious Charge*** until the end of the next player turn. However, if there is an enemy unit within charge range, the unit must attempt to charge it. |
| 18 | **Da Green Tide Rises** | Reinforcements arrive from nowhere. The unit passes its morale test and D3+1 Ork Boyz models (armed with slugga and choppa) are immediately added to the unit, placed in coherency. These models may act normally starting next turn. The unit may not exceed its starting strength from this effect. |
| 19 | **Gork (or Mork) is Watchin'!** | Divine orkish favor. The unit passes its morale test. All models in the unit gain a **6+ invulnerable save** (or improve an existing invulnerable save by 1, to a maximum of 4+) and ***Feel No Pain (6+)*** until the end of the next player turn. The controlling player gains +1 **WAAAGH! ENERGY**. |
| 20 | **WAAAGH!!!** | The failed morale test triggers a localized WAAAGH! The unit passes its morale test and gains ***Fearless***, ***Rage***, ***Furious Charge***, and +1 Attack until the end of the next player turn. Additionally, all friendly Ork units within 12" immediately pass any ongoing morale or pinning tests and gain +1 Attack until the end of the turn. The controlling player gains +3 **WAAAGH! ENERGY**. |

