### WAAAGH! Energy

The collective psychic fury and excitement of an Ork horde is a palpable force — a rising tide of aggression that feeds on violence and builds toward something unstoppable. In OmniHammer, this is represented by **WAAAGH! ENERGY**, an army-wide resource that the Ork player accumulates through acts of violence and spends to unleash powerful effects.

#### Generating WAAAGH! Energy

The Ork player tracks their current WAAAGH! Energy on a counter or die visible to both players. WAAAGH! Energy is generated as follows:

| Trigger | Energy Gained |
| :---- | :---: |
| An Ork unit successfully completes a charge move against an enemy unit | +1 |
| An enemy unit is destroyed (reduced to 0 models or removed from play) by Ork attacks | +D3 |
| An enemy **HQ** unit is destroyed | +3 |
| The enemy **WARLORD** is slain | +5 |

**Rules for Generating Energy:**
- WAAAGH! Energy is generated immediately when the triggering event occurs.
- A single event can only trigger one source of energy generation. If an Ork unit charges and subsequently destroys an enemy unit in the same assault phase, both triggers apply — the charge generates +1, and the destruction generates +D3 (or +3/+5 if the destroyed unit was an HQ/Warlord).
- The Ork player's WAAAGH! Energy has no maximum cap.
- WAAAGH! Energy persists between turns and is never lost unless spent.
- Some results on the **MOB RULE TABLE** also generate WAAAGH! Energy.

#### Spending WAAAGH! Energy

WAAAGH! Energy may be spent **during any phase of the game** to activate effects from the **WAAAGH! ENERGY MENU**. The Ork player declares they are spending WAAAGH! Energy, names the effect, pays the cost, and resolves it immediately. Unless otherwise stated, each effect targets a single friendly Ork unit within 12" of the **WARLORD** or within 6" of any Ork **CHARACTER** model.

**The same effect may not be applied to the same unit more than once per turn.** Different effects may be stacked on the same unit.

**WAAAGH! ENERGY MENU**

| Cost | Name | Phase | Effect |
| :---: | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| 1 | **Get Movin' Ya Gitz!** | Movement | Target unit gains ***Fleet*** until the end of the phase. |
| 1 | **'Old da Line!** | Any | Target unit automatically passes its next **MORALE** or **PINNING** test this turn. |
| 1 | **Dakka Dakka Dakka!** | Shooting | Target unit may re-roll all To Hit rolls of 1 during this shooting phase. |
| 2 | **Stomp 'Arder!** | Assault | Target unit gains +1 Attack until the end of the phase. |
| 2 | **More Dakka!** | Shooting | All Rapid Fire and Assault type weapons in the target unit fire an additional shot this phase (e.g. Rapid Fire 1 becomes Rapid Fire 2 at half range). |
| 2 | **Feel Nuffin'!** | Any | Target unit gains ***Feel No Pain (6+)*** until the end of the turn. If the unit already has ***Feel No Pain***, improve it by 1 (to a maximum of 4+). |
| 2 | **Rev It Up!** | Movement | Target **VEHICLE** or **BIKE** unit adds +D6" to its maximum movement this phase. If the unit rolls a 6 on this die, the vehicle or bike suffers a glancing hit at the end of its movement (something fell off). |
| 3 | **Mob Up!** | Movement | Target unit that is within 2" of another friendly Ork **INFANTRY** unit of the same type may merge with it, forming a single unit. The merged unit uses the higher Leadership value. The combined unit may not exceed 30 models. |
| 3 | **WAAAGH! Strike** | Assault | Target unit gains +1 Strength until the end of the phase. |
| 3 | **Krump 'Em Good!** | Assault | Target unit gains ***Furious Charge*** until the end of the phase. If the unit already has ***Furious Charge***, it gains an additional +1 Strength and +1 Initiative when charging (for a total of +2/+2 from ***Furious Charge***). |
| 3 | **Gork's Fist** | Psychic | Target friendly Ork **PSYKER** may immediately attempt to manifest one additional psychic power this turn, even if it has already manifested its maximum number of powers. The Psyker must still pass the psychic test as normal. |
| 3 | **More Boyz!** | Movement | D6 Ork Boyz models (armed with slugga and choppa) are added to the target **INFANTRY** unit, placed in coherency. These models may act normally starting next turn. The unit may not exceed its starting strength. |
| 4 | **Da Boss is Watchin'!** | Any | Target unit gains ***Fearless*** until the end of the turn. |
| 4 | **We'z Harder Dan You!** | Any | Target unit gains a **6+ invulnerable save** (or improves an existing invulnerable save by 1, to a maximum of 4+) until the end of the turn. |
| 5 | **Ramming Speed!** | Movement | Target Ork **VEHICLE** making a Ram or Tank Shock adds +D6 to its front armor value for resolving the Ram and doubles the Strength of the impact. The vehicle must move at least its full combat speed movement to use this effect. |
| 6 | **DA BIG WAAAGH!** | Start of Turn | All friendly Ork units on the table gain +1 Attack, +1 WS, and ***Furious Charge*** until the end of the turn. This effect does not require range to a CHARACTER. May only be used once per game. |

