## KLANZ OF DA ORKS

When constructing your army list, you must choose one of the following Klanz. Each Klan confers a **Signature Rule** and a **Drawback** to all models with the **Klan Kultur** special rule. Models without **Klan Kultur** (such as Gretchin and certain mercenary units) are not affected by either the Signature Rule or the Drawback.

---

### Goffs — Da 'Ardest Boyz

*"We'z da biggest and da strongest! If you ain't fightin', you ain't nuffin'!"*

The Goffs are the most brutal and warlike of all the Ork Klanz. They hold close combat above all other pursuits and consider shooting to be vaguely unorky — unless it's at point blank range, right before a charge.

**Signature Rule — Born Scrappers:** Goffs models gain +1 WS when locked in close combat with a unit that has a higher WS than them. Additionally, Goffs units that successfully charge gain +1 Attack on the turn they charge (this is cumulative with the normal charge bonus, for a total of +2 Attacks on the charge).

**Drawback — Shootin' is for Grots:** Goffs models suffer -1 BS (to a minimum of 1). This does not apply to weapons fired as part of ***Overwatch*** or ***Stand & Shoot!*** reactions.

---

### Evil Sunz — Da Speed Freeks

*"RED ONES GO FASTA!"*

The Evil Sunz are obsessed with speed. They paint everything red in the unshakeable belief that it makes things go faster — and, terrifyingly, Ork belief being what it is, it might actually work.

**Signature Rule — Red Ones Go Fasta:** Evil Sunz **INFANTRY** models add +1" to their standard movement. Evil Sunz **VEHICLE** and **BIKE** models add +2" to all movement modes. Additionally, Evil Sunz units may ***Turbo-Boost*** or move ***Flat Out*** and still fire Snap Shots in the shooting phase.

**Drawback — Can't Sit Still:** Evil Sunz units that did not move in their movement phase (i.e., they remained stationary) suffer -1 to all To Hit rolls during the shooting phase and -1 WS until the start of their next turn. They're too agitated to fight properly when standing still.

---

### Bad Moons — Da Richest Gitz

*"We got da biggest gunz, da flashiest bitz, and more teef dan you'll ever see!"*

Bad Moons are the wealthiest of Ork Klanz, blessed with the fastest-growing teef and an unquenchable appetite for ostentatious firepower. They festoon their equipment with gold plating, checkered patterns, and impractically large ammunition feeds.

**Signature Rule — Flashy Gitz:** All Ranged weapons carried by Bad Moons models increase their maximum range by 6". Additionally, all Rapid Fire weapons carried by Bad Moons models gain +1 shot at half range (e.g. Rapid Fire 1 becomes Rapid Fire 2 at half range, Rapid Fire 2 becomes Rapid Fire 3 at half range).

**Drawback — 'Eavy Pockets:** Bad Moons models are weighed down by all their flash gear. They suffer -1" to their charge distance rolls and may not use the ***Fleet*** special rule, even if it is granted by another effect (such as WAAAGH! Energy or the Mob Rule table). Bad Moons units may still charge normally — they just can't run and charge.

---

### Deathskulls — Da Lucky Gitz

*"Iz not stealin', it's redistributin'! Gork sez it's mine now."*

Deathskulls are notorious thieves, looters, and scavengers who paint themselves and their gear blue for luck. They have an uncanny knack for finding exactly what they need among the wreckage of battle, and their superstitious rituals seem to pay off with disturbing regularity.

**Signature Rule — Lucky Blue Gitz:** Deathskulls models gain a **6+ invulnerable save**. Additionally, once per turn, the Ork player may re-roll a single die roll made for or against a Deathskulls unit (this includes To Hit, To Wound, saving throws, morale tests, charge distances, etc.). Declare the re-roll before any other dice are rolled.

**Drawback — Sticky Fingerz:** Deathskulls units that end their movement phase within 3" of a destroyed vehicle wreck, crashed flyer, or dead Monstrous Creature must take a Leadership test. If failed, the unit spends the turn looting and may not shoot or charge in that turn. They're too busy nicking bitz.

---

### Blood Axes — Da Sneaky Gitz

*"Tactics iz not un-orky! It's just krumpin' smarter!"*

Blood Axes are considered deeply suspect by other Orks for their willingness to engage in "un-orky" behavior such as retreating, using camouflage, and even negotiating. They are the closest thing Orks have to professional soldiers, which isn't saying much.

**Signature Rule — Taktikal Jeenyus:** Blood Axes units gain ***Scouts*** and ***Move Through Cover***. Additionally, Blood Axes units that choose to voluntarily fall back (before rolling on the Mob Rule Table) may fall back 3D6" and automatically regroup at the end of their fall back move, regardless of being below half strength. They are considered to have executed a "taktikal wivdrawl" and may act normally in their next turn.

**Drawback — Iz Dey Even Orkz?:** Other Orks are suspicious of Blood Axes. Blood Axes units may not benefit from WAAAGH! Energy effects that originate from a CHARACTER that does not have the **Klan Kultur (Blood Axes)** special rule. The army's WAAAGH! Energy generation from charges is reduced to +0 (charges no longer generate WAAAGH! Energy) — Blood Axes charges are too calculated to get the boyz excited.

---

### Snakebites — Da Old Ways

*"We don't need no stinkin' machines! Da old ways is da best ways!"*

Snakebites are traditionalists who reject much of Ork "technology" in favor of beast-riding, squig-herding, and good old-fashioned Orky toughness. They're looked down upon by other Klanz as primitive, but Snakebites don't care — they're tough as nails and their squigs are hungrier than your trukk.

**Signature Rule — 'Ard as Nails:** Snakebites **INFANTRY** and **CAVALRY** models gain +1 Toughness. Additionally, Snakebites models gain ***Feel No Pain (6+)***. Models that already have ***Feel No Pain*** improve it by 1 (to a maximum of 4+).

**Drawback — No Trust in Mekwork:** Snakebites **VEHICLE** models (except Walkers and Chariots) suffer -1 BS and may not fire ***Overwatch***. Snakebites may not take more **VEHICLE** units (excluding Walkers and Chariots) than they have **INFANTRY** or **CAVALRY** units in the same detachment.

---

### Freebooterz — Da Flashest Pirates

*"We fight for whoever's got da most teef! And if dey ain't got enough teef, we take 'em anyway!"*

Freebooterz are Ork mercenaries, pirates, and adventurers who owe allegiance to no Klan. Their warbands are a motley collection of outcasts, fortune-seekers, and Orks who simply enjoy the pirate aesthetic. They fight for pay, plunder, and the sheer thrill of it.

**Signature Rule — Showoffz:** Whenever a Freebooterz unit destroys an enemy unit, all other friendly Freebooterz units that can draw line of sight to the destroyed unit gain +1 BS and +1 WS until the end of the current phase. This effect is cumulative if multiple enemy units are destroyed in the same phase (to a maximum of +3 BS/WS). The boyz get fired up watching their mates krump the enemy.

**Drawback — Pay Day or No Way:** At the start of each of the Ork player's turns, if no enemy units were destroyed during the previous battle round, all Freebooterz units must take a **MORALE** test with a -2 Leadership modifier. If the battle isn't profitable, the boyz start thinking about leaving. This drawback does not apply on the first battle round.

